UMALUSI has confirmed that the matric results will be released by Basic Education Minister Angie Motshekga on Thursday, 19 January. The education quality assurance body announced the news at a media briefing in Tshwane on Monday, 16 January. CEO Mafu Rakometsi said schools started late in 2022 as a result of the Covid-19 pandemic. “As a result, the examinations and processes that flow from the commencement of exams started later than usual,” he said. ALSO READ:ZIYAKHALA: Schools buckling under pressure! He said the approval date was agreed upon by Umalusi and all the assessment bodies in the first half of 2022. “Regarding applications for further or higher education study, you are aware that the system opens in June and closes in September of the preceding year. “Higher education institutions make provisional admission decisions based on the results that learners obtained while in grade 11. Final decisions are taken as soon as the results are submitted,” he said. He said several cases of cheating were uncovered, including the use of crib notes, cellphones in exam centres and answer papers being circulated on WhatsApp groups. He said the culprits had been punished. Professor Yunus Ballim, chairman of Umalusi Council, urged all assessment bodies to ensure that the integrity of the system is protected. Ballim thanked and congratulated all the pupils who succeeded. “To those who have not succeeded, there is another chance for you this year,” he said. You must be SIGNED IN to read comments